    <p id="Par53">We applied the four point estimation methods and the four interval estimation methods to the Graves’ disease data and the MCTFR data for their practical use on the qualitative trait and the quantitative trait, respectively. In the Graves’ disease data application, we found that SNP rs3827440 may undergo the XCI-S pattern towards the allele <italic>C</italic> in the replication stage and the pooled data. Although we did not detect the XCI-S pattern in the GWAS stage, the BN and BU methods still show their superiority by providing shorter HPDIs, compared to the PF and Fieller’s methods. In the MCTFR data application, the <inline-formula id="IEq401"><alternatives><tex-math id="M737">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
